Environment :
-------------
  NSLIB - defines the path to netscale source library (or repository).

Application directory :
-----------------------
  Applications must be named using alphanumeric characters and the
  sub-directory in the source tree, containing the application code, must
  also have same name.

Application supervisor :
------------------------
  Child specifications for application's supervisors are expected to be
  defined in the corresponding application's .app directory. The key,value
  pair defining the childspec should be of the form,

    { <supervisor-proc-name>_sup_childspecs, <childspecs> }

Standard macros :
-----------------

  Every application must define <appname>.hrl file under <appname>/include/
  path. This header file will be used by every module defined under the
  application.

  ?APPNAME - application name.

